	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston</placeName> <date>Decr 8th 1857</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I regret I should have so far neg&#45;<lb/>lected my duty to you when I transmitted<lb/> to your care a communication in which I<lb/> was particularly interested&#44; without directly<lb/> addressing you soliciting your kind interference<lb/> &#38; influence&#44; to aid me in the accomplishment<lb/> of my purpose&#44; this would even of itself<lb/> bear the impression&#44; that I was influenced<lb/> by personal motives&#59; but regardless of this&#44;<lb/> permit me to assure you&#44; that there was<lb/> something due on other grounds&#44; viz&#44; my<lb/> personal respect for your position as a teacher<lb/> in <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; and had it not been that I was<lb/> reminded of the fact of my negligence I<lb/> should still have remained the defaulter&#44;<lb/> although quite unintentional&#59; but&#44; repentance<lb/> never comes too late&#44; and will doubtless<lb/> make reparation for my wrong.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have seen your communica&#45;<lb/>tions to <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName>&#44; by which I am con&#45;<lb/>vinced you have interested yourself in my<lb/> behalf&#44; for which I have to thank you&#44;<lb/> I regret to learn that there has been a division<lb/> in the congregations I should have preferred<lb/> to have heard the &#8220;two sticks were united&#8221;</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>however as congregations are now con&#45;<lb/>stituted I regret to say too much dif&#45;<lb/>ference of feeling exists&#44; &#38; too much dis&#45;<lb/>satisfaction prevails&#44; Alas&#33; For the poor<lb/> Hazanim&#44; our lot is not always cast<lb/> in pleasant places&#44; although we must<lb/> not murmur&#44; I should like to have<lb/> been made aware of the mode of living<lb/> domestic expenses &#38;c&#44; so as to form an<lb/> estimate of situation <hi rend="underline">&#38; place</hi>&#59; but for<lb/> that I of course have to thank myself<lb/> for not seeking your advice in time.<lb/>  I may yet not be too late&#44; could you<lb/> respond to this promptly&#44; I am happy<lb/> to hear my old friend <persName>Revd S. Jacobs</persName> is<lb/> officiating in your city&#44; and I trust<lb/> he may continue long in his occu&#45;<lb/>pation to render the congregation the<lb/> benefit of his valuable services.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Nathan</persName> in his commu&#45;<lb/>nication to you in my behalf&#44; more<lb/> or less represented to you my position<lb/> in the present sphere of my labors&#44;<lb/> and gave you a faithful account<lb/> of the nature of the difficulties under<lb/> which I am now laboring&#44; and I<lb/> feel within myself that nothing but<lb/> a fair field for the <sic>developement</sic> of<lb/> my energies&#8212;which I am impressed</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>with the conviction would be open for<lb/> me in a strange country&#8212;can arouse<lb/> me from my now dormant state&#44;<lb/> to render myself useful to any<lb/> congregation&#44; however praiseworthy is<lb/> modesty&#44; it is too frequently detrimental<lb/> to our interests&#44; yet&#44; we cannot get<lb/> rid of the fact&#59; but that the feeling<lb/> is encouraged.  I however would pursue<lb/> a different course were I to leave this<lb/> for any other place.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Permit me in conclusion<lb/> to thank you for your kind wishes<lb/> to further my purpose&#44; and believe<lb/> me to be</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Thine ever very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">A H DeLevante</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have taken the liberty to enclose a<lb/> letter under your care to <placeName>Richmond</placeName> which I<lb/> would thank you to forward for me</p>
				<p>Not known N E</p>
				<p>Try <placeName>371 Walnut St.</placeName></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
